ompanies and public and private investment managers that has managed to scoop up the majority of the canadian commercial mortgage origination market year over year since the early days of real estate finance a borrowers other option is to finance through a conduit that is a lender who lends with a view to selling the mortgage on or shortly after funding prior to  the majority of commercial mortgages originated by conduit lenders were packaged into cmbs commercial mortgage backed securities pools and sold to institutional investors simply put cmbs is a vehicle through which fixed income investors lend to real estate borrowers originally published in western investor click here to read the full article imc announces first canadian cmbs since  february   institutional mortgage capital canada inc imc is proud to announce it has completed a private placement of commercial mortgage backed securities cmbs with an aggregate principal balance of c  the transaction is the first cmbs deal issued in canada since   the deal entitled institutional mortgage securities canada inc series  imsc  is backed by  loans to two of canadas largest reits riocan reit and calloway reit  the certificates were issued by institutional mortgage securities canada inc an affiliate of imc with td securities as the lead placement agent original story published by cnw click here to read the full story mortgage deal revives stalled securities market january  canada’s moribund commercial mortgagebacked securities market is awakening from a threeyear slumber two major real estate companies are tapping the market for million in the first deal of its kind since  signalling that investors are returning to a sector they had abandoned over worries about the health of the country’s commercial real estate market prior to the recession canadian real estate companies went to the cmbs market for about billion a year in lowcost financing the market literally vanished as lendersretreated and investors shunned higherrisk securities forcing real estate companies to obtain mortgages almost exclusively from large banks the resurgence could make it cheaper for real estate companies to raise the money they need to expand their portfolios driving up property values as more bidders vie forbuildings it will also give investors other than banks the chance to add secured mortgages to their portfolios originally published by ctv click here for the full article copyright  imc limited partnership operating as institutional mortgage capital licensed under the mortgage brokerages lenders and administrators act  license no  privacy policy  terms of use  disclaimer